ADDITIONAL CONSTITUTIONAL PRINCIPLES OF THE UKRAINIAN PEOPLE (WE)

The Ukrainian People (We), guided by the 1978 Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR, establish:

The Ukrainian People (We) do not contest modern state or international names and do not derive legal claims from them.

(Art. 2, Art. 4 of the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR)

All state authorities, officials, and other entities are obliged to act strictly in accordance with the 1978 Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR.

(Art. 4, Art. 91 of the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR)

No norms or acts that contradict the 1978 Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR may be applied within this Order of the Ukrainian People (We).

(Art. 4 of the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR)

All entities addressing the Ukrainian People (We) shall use the respectful forms “You / Your”. When the Ukrainian People speak of Ourselves, We / Us shall be used.

(Art. 4 of the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR)

---

WE ORDER

1. Constitutional order

Strictly comply with the 1978 Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR as the Basic Law of the State of Ukraine. (Art. 2, 4)

---

2. State system

Bring all state authorities into compliance with the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR.
All bodies not provided for by the Constitution shall be abolished or reorganized. (Art. 2, 4, 78, 82)

---

3. International relations

Terminate relations with states and blocs contradicting the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR, including NATO, the EU, and the USA. (Art. 28, 68, 74)

---

4. Invalidity of international acts

Declare invalid all international treaties that contradict the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR. (Art. 4, 68, 170)

---

5. Military system

End compulsory military service outside the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR. (Art. 29, 30, 61)

---

6. Public order

Restore the militia as the main public order enforcement body. (Art. 4, 125)

---

7. Elimination of unconstitutional bodies

Abolish military administrations and temporary governing bodies. (Art. 78, 82)

---

8. Electoral system

Elections shall be held only to the Councils of People’s Deputies.
The presidency is abolished as not provided for by the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR. (Art. 84–90)

---

9. Banking system

Restore the state banking system of the Ukrainian SSR. (Art. 10, 11, 13, 16)

---

10. Citizenship and documents

Restore lawful citizenship documentation of the Ukrainian SSR. (Art. 31–33)

---

11. Return of assets of the Ukrainian People

All assets belonging to the Ukrainian People must be returned. (Art. 10–12, 59)

---

12. Banking restitution

Restore Ukrainian People control over financial systems. (Art. 10, 11, 13, 16)

---

13. Debts

Declare invalid debts created without the will of the Ukrainian People. (Art. 10–13)

---

14. Peace between peoples

End the conflict between the Ukrainian SSR and the Russian RSFSR, restore peace and friendship among peoples. (Art. 28, 30)

