RESPONSIBILITY

Failure to comply with this Order constitutes a violation of the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR and the will of the Ukrainian People. (Art. 2, 4, 91–96)

Any human, person, official, organization, corporation, state body, private actor, or entity acting against the lawful Order of the Ukrainian People (We) shall bear responsibility according to the 1978 Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR.

---

ADDITIONAL LIABILITY CLAUSE

Any human, person, official, organization, corporation, state body, private actor, or entity that contests, obstructs, ignores, falsifies, or acts against this lawful Order of the Ukrainian People (We), without lawful constitutional authority under the 1978 Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR, shall bear personal responsibility for all resulting damages, losses, unlawful enrichment, and violations against the Ukrainian People (We).
Claims for compensation, restitution, reparations, and material liability may be asserted personally against such actors in full amount without limitation including the equivalent value of five trillion tons of gold.
(Art. 4, Art. 57–59, Art. 91–96 of the Constitution of the Ukrainian SSR)

